description: Duel tells the story of how skill, brute force and cunning all determine who lives and who dies - all told in 100% pure, relentless, cover-to-cover action. Aircraft, battleship, submarine, helicopter, motorcycle, or just hand-to-hand combat, Duel has it all. Duel #0 debuts in style with stunning art by fan-favorite Joe Wight (Star Wars, Robotech) in an issue pitting an American mercenary pilot from the Flying Tigers in his Curtis P-40 Warhawk against a seasoned Japanese warrior in his Nakajima Ki-43 Hayabusa (Zero) in the skies of China on Christmas Day.

person_credits.name: Bill Watterson
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: While the USAF Special Forces are supporting the Army's Operation: Mongoose, their main battle over the mountains to flush out the terrorists, a lone modified Blackhawk (the USAF Special Forces' Pavehawk version), carrying a female news reporter, encounters a renegade Hind-E manned by special Al Quaeda crew bent on assassinating Pakistan's President. It's up to the Blackhawk's crew to stop them!

When the Argentine forces took over the Falkland Islands by force in 1982, the Argentines realized a century-old dream, but the British weren't going to take it sitting down. On May 1st, the Argentine carrier, 25 de Mayo, was ready to strike the British fleet, but lack of wind was going to stop them. Yet the winds of war were on the Argentine side this time, resulting in a new and deadlier suicide war.

Germany: 1945. It is the end of the Third Reich, but the war is not yet over. With the introduction of the new German flying wing, the Horton Ho-229A-1, the most advanced of the new jet fighters, the Americans respond with their P-72 "Super-Thunderbolt," the most powerful of the piston-engine-powered fighters. In real history, both were in the prototype stage and flying when the war ended before they could be deployed. In this "what if" scenario, the combat takes place in the sky above Berlin!

In Hueco Mundo, the rescue party lead by Ichigo battles Quilge Opie, sadistic Quincy loyal to the Vandenreich. In the meantime, the Emperor and his Stern Ritter begin their massive offensive against Soul Society, killing thousands and battling the Captains of the Gotei 13.

name: March of the Starcross

description: This is a tale of war in a desperate future. Giant mechanized warriors are locked in perpetual struggle, but it's the feeling core, the pilots, who fuel the war. What motivates Shon, a young woman living in poverty, to sign away her freedom to face almost certain death?

In the staggering wreckage of Earth's future, the great King Hrothgar and his armies have known only victory after bloody victory. Now they have awakened the ancient evil of the Grendel and are powerless to defend themselves against the demon's wraith! Only with the aid of the young hero Beowulf and a cunning trap can they hope to kill Grendel and finally know peace.

From the creator of Dragon Arms and Oz: The Manga comes a revolutionary vision of this epic tale! The brutal carnage on display last issue was only the beginning! With Grendel wounded and on the run, Hrothgar and his men regroup and prepare to help Beowulf deliver the final blow. A swath of destruction is cut in a last-ditch battle to end Grendel's reign of terror!

Climactic last issue! Believing Grendel to be fatally wounded and near death, Beowulf ventures into the creature's last sanctuary. There he hopes finally to destroy Grendel, and end the horror once and for all. Instead, Beowulf is forced into mortal combat with a nightmare far more ancient and deadly than anything the world has faced before.

Prepare for World War D! We thought the dinosaurs were all gone. We were dead wrong! 65 million years ago, a species of evolved dinosaurs left our Earth, and now they're back! It's the Jurassic War of the Worlds as these Neosaurs commence a massive invasion to reclaim their planet and make mankind extinct!

volume.name: DinoWars: Jurassic War of the Worlds

description: 100 million years ago, the dinosaurs evolved intelligence and escaped into space to avoid the Ice Age. Now they've returned, and they're bent on the extinction of Man! Astronaut Hank Armstrong struggles to save a convoy from biomechanical Jurassic weapons. On the other side of the world, Debra McDonald, a waitress with a dead-end job, encounters a different species of dinosaur. Will these newcomers make a difference? And if so, can they do it in the few hours left before Humanity is wiped out?

volume.name: DinoWars: Jurassic War of the Worlds

description: The intelligent dinosaurs have launched their assault to reclaim Earth! Commander Hank Armstrong organizes the resistance to the invaders. Meanwhile, peaceable dinosaurs contact waitress Deb MacDonald to negotiate a treaty, even as their warlike brethren pound Earth's nations senseless! Can we survive?

volume.name: DinoWars: Jurassic War of the Worlds

description: Final Issue Rampage! As the world teeters on the brink of dino-fueled destruction, the UN meeting with the Triassians is interrupted by a Megasaur attack! Hank, Deb, and their new friends escape into a secret underground base where human scientists are developing a weapon that just might turn the tide of the war. But if Hank can't deploy the weapon in time, the dinosaurs might make mankind extinct!

volume.name: DinoWars: Jurassic War of the Worlds

description: Prepare for World War D! We thought the dinosaurs were all gone. We were dead wrong. About 65 million years ago, a species of evolved dinosaurs left our Earth, and now they're back! It's the Jurassic War of the Worlds as these Neosaurs commence a massive invasion to reclaim their planet and make Mankind extinct! Don't miss out on this action-packed story by celebrated creator Rod Espinosa that will give a whole new meaning to the term "D-Day!"

volume.name: DinoWars: Jurassic War of the Worlds

name: The Mystery of the Island of Dogs pt. 2

description:
Yoann Vulture sorcerer Horus, a ladykiller? Who knew? Yet, he is accused of impregnating a slew of women.

The second story takes a much lighter tone starring Grogro the big always hungry goofball seen in many stories before, especially in the Parade series.

Here, he's the hero, or at least tries to be, on a mission to fix a mess with a bunch of beer brewers. Question is: will he solve the problem - or just eat (and drink) it?
name: Night of the Ladykiller

description: In the tradition of Lord of the Rings, Bastard!! and Dark Angel comes the ultimate tale of swords and sorcery! Millennia ago, the Dragon Kings held the world in their iron grip. The most powerful warriors waged a final battle against these monsters and freed humanity. Now, a new breed of warriors must destroy the corrupt heroes of old, who have become as hideous and tyrannical as the kings they once overthrew! Five legendary heroes have been assembled by the ancient wizard Anrack, who instructs them in the use of the Dragon Arms - powerful and ageless weapons. But even new blood and steel may not be enough to topple the indestructible might of timeless masters of death!

In the first issue, an entire city-state was destroyed. Now, the continent upon which it sat is also threatened! The world waits in silence as each unstoppable soldier of war raises the stakes in an earth-shattering bid to survive!

After releasing Stone from the control of the Majin, the battle-hardened group head for the first confrontation with the Dragon King Ravenesque. Meanwhile, Anrack begins to wonder if the heroes can be trusted to give up their new powers when the war ends.

The secret behind the creation of the Dragon Arms is revealed as Anrack and his warriors travel deeper into the lands controlled by the Dragon Kings. During their march, they are subjected to the ever-growing horrors of the Majin and the suffering of the innocents who have no escape.
Stone reveals his true power. Will he aid the heroes in their time of need, or join in the corruption of the Dragon Kings? Meanwhile, Captain Seele heads for his confrontation with General Ades.

As Seele continues his quest, the Heroes' fight against the Fallen Kings rages on. The battle is joined by Eon and his high generals. Can these masters of darkness be overthrown by the masters of war?
Actually issue 1953 1-2

description: Battle Girlz follows the adventures of a team of supreme heroines: Expert Mech Girl, Super Mighty Girl, Powerful Priestess, Nerdy Gadgeteer and Seductive Temptress. They have been gathered together by a legendary goddess to live in her strange mansion and to fight evil across the universe and beyond!

Betti lands on the planet Darvak in search of the Van Goths' kidnapped child, Bractchal. While searching the Van Goth chemical engineering plant, she quickly runs into trouble as the Intergalactic Royal Police pop in. If that wasn¹t enough, she also discovers that the Vampericons, the deadliest alien race ever recorded by intelligent life forms, have infested the entire plant! Oh yeah, her sidekick Croaker runs into some Martian hookers. Don¹t miss this action-packed second issue of the deadliest ray-gun-packin¹ mercenary in space, Betti Cozmo!

In this action-packed finale to the critically acclaimed mini-series, Betti Cozmo and Bractchal, the missing child she was hired to retrieve, must race against time and fight off an army of bloodsucking aliens! After breaking free from the Vampericons, Betti grabs the kid and deftly maneuvers through the chemical engineering plant while blasting anything that hisses and has really big teeth. However, time is of the essence for our heroine, as a bomb is set to destroy the entire plant and everything in it. This is the only method to ensure that there will be no further spread of the deadly Vampericons!

How does America stop terrorists from getting into our nation via Canada? By using a highly trained Canadian counter-terrorist unit. They've been instructed by the finest Special Forces groups in the world, but can they outthink or outgun a threat to the U.S. that may have domestic ties?

The full-auto action and intrigue continues as the CTF-3 team attempts to thwart a cell of terrorists from unleashing a tide of destruction upon America! But how will the team succeed if politics and corruption within their midst interferes?

The intrigue & action hit full-auto as Joint Task Force 3 confront the most lethal adversaries on Earth, a splinter cell of elite U.S. Special forces! Does JTF-3 have a chance, or will North America be destroyed from within?

The action is non-stop and relentless as the JTF-3 team gun their way to the truth behind the terrorist plot to destroy North America. A cautionary tale that may prove too close to reality to pass as fiction, if your flavor is anime action, Counter Ops is number one with a bullet!

Ignatz and Eisner nominee Rod Espinosa's critically acclaimed series returns for its final chapter. Princess Mabelrose is not like any other fairytale princess. She isn't the fairest in the land and she bungled her first ball and the prince would not dance with her. Kidnapped by the evil dragon and not wanting to wait for a prince to rescue her, she did what no other fairy tale princess has ever done: she boldly escaped on her own! With the aid of Spiky, a friendly talking porcupine, they found temporary solace with the Munken people. But safety was only temporary; they had to move on to prevent the evil dragon from catching up and locating them. The Munkens advised them to seek the kingdom of Leptia. Only, once they arrive, will Mabelrose and Spiky be safe? What are the dragon's plans? What secrets lay undiscovered in the kingdom that lies before them?

volume.name: The Courageous Princess: The Kindgom of Leptia
